The paper discusses graph neural networks and their applications in various domains such as physics, molecular fingerprints, protein interface prediction, disease classification, and reasoning on extracted structures like dependency trees and scene graphs. These domains are closely related to machine learning subfields such as deep learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
